
<h1 id="nps-api-accesscontrolpolicy">AccessControlPolicy</h1>

## List the names and ids for the access policies. Administrators are able to view all policies.
Access policy permissions can limit non-administrator access to specific policies for non-administrator users.

<a id="opIdListNamesAsync"></a>

> Code samples

```shell
# You can also use wget
curl -X GET /api/v1/AccessControlPolicy/Names \
  -H 'Accept: text/plain' \
  -H 'Authorization: API_KEY'

```

```powershell
Invoke-RestMethod -Method GET -Url /api/v1/AccessControlPolicy/Names 

```

```python
import requests
headers = {
  'Accept': 'text/plain',
  'Authorization': 'API_KEY'
}

r = requests.get('/api/v1/AccessControlPolicy/Names', headers = headers)

print(r.json())

```

`GET /api/v1/AccessControlPolicy/Names`

> Example responses

> 200 Response

```
[{"id":"497f6eca-6276-4993-bfeb-53cbbbba6f08","name":"string"}]
```

```json
[
  {
    "id": "497f6eca-6276-4993-bfeb-53cbbbba6f08",
    "name": "string"
  }
]
```

## Retrieve all policies.

<a id="opIdGetAll"></a>

> Code samples

```shell
# You can also use wget
curl -X GET /api/v1/AccessControlPolicy \
  -H 'Accept: text/plain' \
  -H 'Authorization: API_KEY'

```

```powershell
Invoke-RestMethod -Method GET -Url /api/v1/AccessControlPolicy 

```

```python
import requests
headers = {
  'Accept': 'text/plain',
  'Authorization': 'API_KEY'
}

r = requests.get('/api/v1/AccessControlPolicy', headers = headers)

print(r.json())

```

`GET /api/v1/AccessControlPolicy`

<h3 id="retrieve-all-policies.-parameters">Parameters</h3>

|Name|In|Type|Required|Description|
|---|---|---|---|---|
|isDeleted|query|boolean|false|If true only returns deleted policies|
|isDisabled|query|boolean|false|If true only returns disabled policies|
|ignoreStatus|query|boolean|false|If true return all policies, ignoring deleted/disabled status|

```shell
# You can also use wget
curl -X GET /api/v1/AccessControlPolicy/{accessControlPolicyId} \
```

```powershell
Invoke-RestMethod -Method GET -Url /api/v1/AccessControlPolicy/{accessControlPolicyId}
```

```python
import requests
headers = {
  'Accept': 'text/plain',

}
```

```shell
# You can also use wget
curl -X DELETE /api/v1/AccessControlPolicy/{accessControlPolicyId} \
  -H 'Authorization: API_KEY'

```

```powershell
Invoke-RestMethod -Method DELETE -Url /api/v1/AccessControlPolicy/{accessControlPolicyId} 

```

```python
import requests
headers = {

}

r = requests.delete('/api/v1/AccessControlPolicy/{accessControlPolicyId}', headers = headers)
```

> Code samples

```shell
# You can also use wget
curl -X PUT /api/v1/AccessControlPolicy/{accessControlPolicyId} \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json-patch+json' \
  -H 'Accept: text/plain' \
  -H 'Authorization: API_KEY'

```

```python
}
```

## Change policy delete/disabled status.

<a id="opIdPutStatus"></a>

> Code samples

```shell
# You can also use wget
curl -X PUT /api/v1/AccessControlPolicy/{accessControlPolicyId}/Status \
  -H 'Accept: text/plain' \
  -H 'Authorization: API_KEY'

```

```powershell
Invoke-RestMethod -Method PUT -Url /api/v1/AccessControlPolicy/{accessControlPolicyId}/Status 

```

```python
import requests
headers = {
  'Accept': 'text/plain',
  'Authorization': 'API_KEY'
}

r = requests.put('/api/v1/AccessControlPolicy/{accessControlPolicyId}/Status', headers = headers)

print(r.json())

```

`PUT /api/v1/AccessControlPolicy/{accessControlPolicyId}/Status`

|Name|In|Type|Required|Description|
|---|---|---|---|---|
|accessControlPolicyId|path|string(uuid)|true|none|
|isDeleted|query|boolean|false|none|
|isDisabled|query|boolean|false|none|

## Retrieve policies by managed account/managed resource id pair, which is what happens in a flip.

<a id="opIdFindPolicies"></a>

> Code samples

```shell
# You can also use wget
curl -X GET /api/v1/AccessControlPolicy/ManagedAccount/{managedAccountId}/ManagedResource/{managedResourceId} \
  -H 'Accept: text/plain' \
  -H 'Authorization: API_KEY'

```

```powershell
Invoke-RestMethod -Method GET -Url /api/v1/AccessControlPolicy/ManagedAccount/{managedAccountId}/ManagedResource/{managedResourceId} 

```

```python
import requests
headers = {
  'Accept': 'text/plain',
  'Authorization': 'API_KEY'
}

r = requests.get('/api/v1/AccessControlPolicy/ManagedAccount/{managedAccountId}/ManagedResource/{managedResourceId}', headers = headers)

print(r.json())

```
